INSTALL : sudo apt install john

AUTOMATE CRACKING : john --wordlist=/Path/Wordlist /path/Filename

INSTALL HASH IDENTIFIER : wget https://gitlab.com/kalilinux/packages/hash-identifier/-/raw/kali/master/hash-id.py

LAUNCH HASH IDENTIFIER : python3 hash-id.py

FORMAT SPECIFIC CRACKING : john --format=Give_Hash_Format --wordlist=/Path/Wordlist /path/Filename

LIST ALL FORMATS : john --list=formats

GET DESIRED HASH TYPE : john --list=formats | grep -iF "HashType"


UNSHADOW : 

    unshadow etc_passwd_copy etc_shadow_copy > unshadowed.txt

    COMMAND : john --wordlist=/Path/wordlist --format=Hash_Format unshadowed.txt


SINGLE CRACK MODE : 

    PREPEND FILE : Username:Remaining_hashes

    SYNTAX : john --single --format=Hash_format /Path/Filename


PASSWORD COMPLEXITY PREDICTIBILTY AND CUSTOM RULES : 

    The first line : [List.Rules:Name_rules]

    Az: Takes the word and appends it with the characters you define
    A0: Takes the word and prepends it with the characters you define
    c: Capitalises the character positionally

    [0-9]: Will include numbers 0-9
    [0]: Will include only the number 0
    [A-z]: Will include both upper and lowercase
    [A-Z]: Will include only uppercase letters
    [a-z]: Will include only lowercase letters
    [a]: Will include only a
    [!£$%@]: Will include the symbols !, £, $, %, and @

COMMAND : john --wordlist=/path/wordlist --rule=Name_rules /Path/FileName


ZIP2JOHN : 

    GET HASH : zip2john -Options /Path/ZipFileName > Zip_hash.txt

    COMMAND :  john --wordlist=/Path/wordlist Zip_hash.txt


RAR2JOHN :

    GET HASH : rar2john /Path/RARFile > rar_hash.txt

    COMMAND : john --wordlist=/Path/Wordlist rar_hash.txt

    UNRAR A FILE : unrar Filename.rar


SSH2JOHN : 

    GET HASH : ssh2john /Path/id_rsa_privateKeyFile > hashed.txt

    COMMAND : john --wordlist=/Path/Wordlist hashed.txt

    
